cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the conflict between privacy and trust and proposes a solution to resolve it using trustworthy hardware. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of client-side hardware to realize the proposed architecture. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of cloud services in contrast to client-side hardware. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper proposes a software architecture to resolve the privacy-trust conflict. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of privacy and trust on user contributions to online services.
